  ('antecedent', 'adj.', '在先前的；前身的 先例、祖先', 'preceding in time or order; previous or preexisting; n. thing or circumstance that is or comes before another', 'We must accept that nothing is or can be unhinged (脫鉤) from causal (因果) sequence: every event has its antecedent cause, however murky (不清楚的；隱晦的). - Patheos (blog)', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 7 / 字根 ante, anti 先前 / 提示 antique 古代的、古董'),
