  ('antiseptic', 'n.', '抗菌的、防腐的', 'substance that prevents a wound, etc from becoming septic, esp by destroying bacteria', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'anti(反) + sept(細菌) + ic → 殺菌劑', 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 77 / 字根 sept 細菌、腐爛 / 提示 septic 受感染的、腐敗的'),
  ('antithetical', null, '相反的、對立的', null, 'The debilitating after-effects of trauma are antithetical to the American idea that people can pull themselves up by their bootstraps, Henry said. 精神創傷造成的虛弱效應對立於美國認為人們可以自己振作起來的理想', array['n. antithesis']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 7'),
