  ('aphorism', 'n.', '格言、警句、箴言', 'short wise saying; maxim', 'An aphorism is a concise, terse, laconic, and/or memorable expression of a general truth or principle. E.g. "Power tends to corrupt, and absolute power corrupts absolutely."', array['maxim', 'adage', 'axiom', 'dictum']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 42'),
