  ('blithe', 'adj.', '無憂的、快樂的', 'lacking due thought or consideration : CASUAL, HEEDLESS; of a happy lighthearted character or disposition', 'arrived late in his usual blithe way 他一如往常地無憂快樂地遲到了', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 35'),
  ('blockbuster', null, '巨型炸彈、一鳴驚人的事物', 'a large bomb used to demolish extensive areas', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 11 / 字根 bust 爆炸 / 提示 blockbuster 巨型炸彈、一鳴驚人的事物'),
  ('blunder', 'n.', 'v. 犯大錯 n. 愚蠢的大錯', 'stupid or careless mistake', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '笨愣的', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 101 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('bogus', 'adj.', '假冒的、偽造的', 'not genuine : COUNTERFEIT, SHAM', 'The website was shut down for selling bogus products. 這個網站因販賣假冒產品而被關閉。', array['artificial', 'fake', 'sham']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'bonus(獎金) → bogus偽造的獎金', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 50'),
  ('bolster', 'v.', 'v. 支持、鼓勵、增強 n. 長枕', 'support or strengthen', 'The fall in interest rates is starting to bolster investors'' confidence 利率的下滑開始支持投資人的信心', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 11'),
  ('bombastic', null, '誇誇其談的', 'exaggerated importance by artificial or empty means', 'a bombastic speech 誇大其辭的演說', array['pompous']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 35'),
  ('boon', 'n.', '好處、利益、恩惠', 'request or favour (used esp with the vs shown)', 'Presidential endorsements 來自總統的背書 can be a great boon to political candidates who are competing in a place where the commander-in-chief is popular and who perhaps need a little boost to get over the finish line.', array['benediction', 'benefit']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 11 / 字根 bon 好 / 提示 bon voyage 一路順風'),
  ('boorish', 'adj.', '粗野的、粗魯的', 'of or like a boor', 'His boorish behavior at the dinner party offended many of the guests. 他在晚宴上的粗鄙行為冒犯了許多客人。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'bear(熊) 很boorish(粗野的)', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 101 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('bounteous', 'adj.', '慷慨的、豐富的', '(of a person) generous', 'nature''s bounty 大自然的慷慨贈與 offered a bounteous reward for finding the lost ring 為找到丟失的戒指提供慷慨的報酬', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 11 / 字根 bon 好 / 提示 bon voyage 一路順風'),
  ('bourgeois', null, '中產階級的人、庸俗的人', null, null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 101 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('braggart', 'n.', 'n. 吹牛者 a. 吹牛的', 'person who brags', 'John is such a braggart; he can''t seem to stop talking about all the money he''s made and how successful he is.', array['v. brag 自誇']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 50'),
  ('brandish', 'v.', '揮舞（武器）、展示', 'wave in a triumphant or threatening way; display', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 101 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('bravado', 'n.', '虛張聲勢', 'display of boldness', 'His bravado was just a cover for his insecurity. 他的虛張聲勢只是掩蓋他的不安全感', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'bravo(喝采聲) + do(作) → 作出來的喝彩聲 → 虛張聲勢', 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 66'),
  ('brazen', 'adj.', '厚顏無恥的', 'shameless; insolent', 'a brazen lie // brazen cheating 明目張膽的作弊', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'braze 黃銅', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 101 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('brevity', 'n.', '簡潔、簡練', 'shortness or briefness', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 55'),
  ('bristle', 'n.', 'n. 短且硬之毛 v. 發怒、毛髮直立', 'short stiff hair', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '音讀：不爽', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 102 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的');
