  ('conflate', 'v.', '合併', 'combine into one; to combine (things, such as two readings of a text) into a composite whole', 'The speaker tended to conflate two separate issues, causing misunderstanding. 講者傾向將兩個不同的問題混為一談，導致誤 解。 || He conflated Islam (the religion) with "Islamism" (an ideology that has sometimes led to violence).', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'con(共同) + flat(吹氣) + e → 吹到一起 → 合併', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 38'),
