  ('connive', 'v.', '縱容；默許；串通的', 'to pretend ignorance of or fail to take action against something one ought to oppose', 'conniving stepmother 縱容的繼母 The government connived 縱容 in the rebels'' military buildup.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'con(全部) + niv(ㄋㄞ 撒嬌) → 整個人都來撒嬌 → 縱容的、默許的', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 51'),
  ('connotation', 'n.', '含蓄、言外之意', 'idea which a word makes one think of in addition to the main meaning', 'In some countries, the word for propaganda (政治宣傳) literally means to spread information, and does not carry any negative connotations.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 56 / 字根 not 標示、記號 / 提示 notice 注意'),
