  ('contingent', 'adj.', 'adj. 依情況而定的；n. 意外事故、偶然事件', 'dependent on or conditioned by something else', 'The time of his arrival is contingent on the weather. 他到達的時間要視天氣條件而定', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 64'),
  ('contravene', 'v.', '違背（法規、習俗）', 'act or be contrary to (a law, etc); break', 'If you contravene the rules, you may face serious consequences. 如果你違反規則，你可能會面臨嚴重後果。', array['breach', 'break', 'fracture', 'infringe', 'offend', 'traduce', 'transgress', 'violate']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'contra(反) + ven(來) + e', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 48'),
  ('contrite', 'adj.', '悔罪的、痛悔的', 'filled with or showing deep regret for having done wrong; repentant', 'She had trouble in accepting a religion that would allow contrite evil-doers access to heaven. 他很難接受一個讓懺悔的作惡者有 途徑去天堂的宗教', array['penitent']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 48'),
  ('contrive', 'v.', '設計、圖謀', 'plan (sth) cleverly or deceitfully; invent; design', 'He contrived a way to escape from the prison.', array['concoct', 'construct', 'devise', 'make up']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 51'),
  ('contumacious', 'adj.', '違抗的、不服從的', 'obstinate and disobedient', 'When we are young (under 30) we are prone to take risks and love speed and unfortunately this age group is very prone to atrocious (惡劣的；差勁的) and contumacious bad driving. - www.timesofmalta.com', array['defiant', 'disobedient', 'incompliant', 'insubordinate', 'intractable', 'recalcitrant', 'refractory', 'restive', 'unruly']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 64'),
