  ('deference', 'n.', '尊敬', 'giving way to the views, wishes, etc of others, usu out of respect; respect', 'They were married in church out of deference to their parents'' wishes. 他們遵從父母的願望，在教堂舉行了婚禮 // Deference to leaders and intolerance toward outsiders (and toward "enemies within") are hallmarks of tribalism 部落文化的特徵是尊敬領導與對 外人(和內部的敵人)不寬容', array['respect', 'veneration']::text[], array['effrontery(厚顏無恥', '放肆)']::text[], '形近reverence尊敬', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 13'),
