  ('disdain', 'n.', '輕蔑、鄙視', 'feeling that sb/sth is not good enough to deserve one''s respect; contempt', '(1) He puts a lot of weight on loyalty, and he disdains disloyalty. (2) Philistine (庸俗的人) hide no secret his disdain 鄙視、厭惡 of aesthetic endeavor. 努力、付出(efforts).', array['scorn', 'despise', 'spurn']::text[], array['respect', 'admire', 'praise']::text[], 'dis(=against) + dain(高貴的 → 使不高貴 → 輕蔑、鄙視', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 4'),
