  ('dismiss', 'v.', '讓…離開；把…打發走；使…離職', 'sb remove sb (esp an employee) from a position; to reject serious consideration of', 'A full investigation was dismissed as unnecessary. 完整調查被稱不需要 || The boss decided to dismiss the employee for repeatedly arriving late to work. 老板決定解雇因為反覆遲到上班的員工。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 41'),
  ('disparage', 'v.', '貶抑、輕蔑', 'suggest, esp unfairly, that is of little value or importance', 'Voters don''t like political advertisements in which opponents disparage one another. 選民不喜歡那些互相彼此攻擊貶抑的政治 廣告 The article disparaged polo as a game for the wealthy. 這文章將馬球貶抑為有錢人的遊戲', array['slight']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 10'),
