  ('elated', 'adj.', '興高采烈的、得意的', 'in high spirits; very happy or proud', 'Alec felt elated—it was the first time that the stallion (種馬、雄馬) hadn''t drawn back (退縮) into the stall (馬廄) at the sight of him. - Walter Farley, The Black Stallion', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 44 / 字根 lev 舉、升、使…輕 / 提示 elevator 電梯'),
  ('electorate', 'n.', '選民、選區', 'all the qualified electors considered as a group', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 43 / 字根 lect 選、選擇 / 提示 election 選舉'),
  ('elegy', 'n.', '輓歌、哀歌', 'poem or song expressing sorrow, esp for the dead; lament', 'After her grandmother''s passing, she wrote an elegy to honor her memory. 她寫了一首輓歌以紀念關於祖母的記憶', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'elegy音讀「哎，樂極」 → 哀嘆去極樂世界了 → 輓歌、悲歌', 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 67'),
  ('elevate', 'v.', '舉起、抬起、使上升', 'sb/sth (fml ) lift sb/sth up; raise sb/sth to a higher place or rank', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 44 / 字根 lev 舉、升、使…輕 / 提示 elevator 電梯'),
  ('elicit', 'v.', '引出、誘出', 'sth (fml ) draw (facts, a response, etc) from sb, sometimes with difficulty', 'The program also showed an awkward moment of Trump reaching out to shake the hand of a North Korean general who instead saluted the American president, eliciting giggles (咯咯地笑) from North Koreans watching the program. 這節目也展示一個尷尬場 景：當川普伸手想與北韓將軍握手時，北韓將軍與他敬禮，引出看節目的北韓人民的咯咯笑聲', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 20'),
  ('eloquence', 'n.', '雄辯、口才', 'expressive language, esp to impress or persuade an audience', 'His eloquence during the speech moved the audience to tears. 他在演講中的雄辯，感動了觀眾落淚。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 40'),
  ('elucidate', 'v.', '闡明、說明', 'make (sth) clear; explain', 'They would not elucidate further.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 40'),
  ('elude', 'v.', '逃避、躲避', 'escape (sb/sth), esp by a trick or cleverness; avoid', 'He tried to elude the security men by sneaking through a back door', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 8'),
  ('elusive', 'adj.', '逃避的、躲避的、難以表述的、難懂的', 'tending to escape or disappear; difficult to capture', 'The more material you uncover, the more elusive your subject becomes.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 46 / 字根 lud, lus 玩、遊戲、扮演 / 提示 illusion 假象、錯覺'),
  ('emanate', 'v.', '散發、發出', 'to come out from a source; EMIT', 'desperation emanation 絕望散發', array['cast', 'discharge', 'emit', 'exhale', 'expel', 'give out', 'vent']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 59'),
  ('emancipate', 'v.', '解放、解除', 'sb set sb free, esp from political, legal or social restrictions', 'emancipate sb. from slavery', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'e(出) + man(手) + cip(拿) + ate → 使手中的東西放下 → 解除', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 17 / 字根 cip 拿、取 / 提示 anticipate 預期、期待'),
  ('embargo', 'n.', '禁運令、封港令', '(on sth) official order that forbids sth, esp trade, the movement of ships, etc', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'em + bar(阻攔) + go(去)', 2, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 10 / 字根 bar 棒子、障礙、律師 / 提示 barrier 障礙物、關卡'),
  ('embellish', 'v.', '美化、裝飾', 'sth make sth beautiful by adding ornaments, etc', 'a book embellished with illustrations 用很多圖示、插圖所裝飾的書', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 16'),
  ('embody', 'v.', '具體實現、體現', 'sth (in sth) (fml ) express or give visible form to (ideas, feelings, etc)', 'The poet embodied her ideas in words. 體現想法 The firefighters embodied courage during the disaster. 體現勇氣', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 19'),
