  ('epitome', 'n.', '典型、摘要', 'a typical or ideal example : EMBODIMENT; thing that shows on a small scale all the characteristics of sth much larger', 'the British monarchy itself is the epitome of tradition. 英國君主制是傳統的體現', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'epi(在…之上) + tome(切割) → 修剪而成的', 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 24'),
  ('equable', 'adj.', '穩定的、不變的', 'free from extremes of heat or cold; moderate', 'an equable man 冷靜的 // an equable climate 平穩的', array['even-tempered', 'calm', 'composed', 'collected', 'nonchalant', 'insouciant']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 27 / 字根 equ 相等、公平 / 提示 equal 相等的'),
  ('equanimity', 'n.', '鎮定、沉著', 'calmness of mind or temper', 'She confronted the daily crises with equanimity. 他以沈著面對每天的危機', array['composure', 'calm', 'tranquility', 'imperturbability', 'aplomb']::text[], array['anxiety']::text[], '事情發生了自己仍然和之前相同 → 沉著', 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 57'),
