  ('exemplify', 'v.', '是…的典型；作為…的例子', 'be a typical example of (sth)', 'The city''s economic growth is exemplified by the many new buildings that are currently under construction. 本城市經濟成長體現 於很多新建築正在蓋', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 25'),
  ('exempt', 'adj.', '免除、豁免', 'free from an obligation, duty or payment; not liable', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'ex(出) + empt(拿、買) → 拿出去 → 免除', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 26 / 字根 empt 拿、買 / 提示 exempt 免除、豁免'),
  ('exert', 'v.', '運用（力量）', 'sth bring (a quality, skill, pressure, etc) into use; apply sth', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 27 / 字根 ert 力量、動 / 提示 exert 運用（力量）'),
