  ('explicit', 'adj.', '詳盡的、清楚的、明確的', '(of a statement, etc) clearly and fully expressed', 'explicit instructions', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 5'),
  ('expurgate', 'v.', '刪除、使純潔', 'remove improper or objectionable parts from (a book, etc)', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 71 / 字根 pur, purg 純潔、清洗 / 提示 purify 使純潔、淨化'),
  ('extant', 'adj.', '尚存的、現存的', 'still in existence', 'extant manuscripts', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'ex(往外) + stant(=stand站) → 能站到現在的 → 現存的', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 82 / 字根 sta, st 站 / 提示 obstacle 障礙、干擾'),
  ('extemporize', null, '即席發言、即興演奏', 'to do something extemporaneously:IMPROVISE; especially :to speak extemporaneously', 'As a skilled speaker, he was able to extemporize his speech. 作為一位熟練的演講者，他能夠即興發言。', array['improvise']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'ex(出) + tempor(時間) + ize → 在安排時間之外演講或表演 → 即席發言、即興演奏', 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 64'),
  ('extenuate', 'v.', '掩飾、減輕罪過', 'make (wrongdoing) less serious (by providing an excuse)', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '使薄、使微不足道', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 86 / 字根 tenu 薄 / 提示 tenuous 稀薄的、空洞的'),
  ('exterminate', 'v.', '消滅、滅絕', 'destroy completely (a race or group of people or animals); wipe out', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 86 / 字根 term 邊界、結束 / 提示 terminate 終止、結束'),
  ('extirpate', 'v.', '消滅、根除', 'remove or destroy (sth) completely', 'The government has launched a campaign to extirpate all illegal drugs from the country.政府發起了一場運動，要從該國徹底 根除所有非法藥物。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 107 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('extol', 'v.', '讚美、頌揚', 'sb (as sth) (fml ) praise (sb/sth) highly', 'He keeps extolling the merits of his new car. 他不斷讚美他新車的優點。', array['praise', 'glorify', 'eulogize', 'laud', 'compliment', 'exalt']::text[], array['lambaste(指責)', 'pan(譴責)']::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 32'),
  ('extort', 'v.', '勒索、敲詐', 'sth obtain sth by violence, threats, etc', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 87 / 字根 tort 扭、彎曲 / 提示 distort 扭曲、弄歪  tornado 龍捲風  torture 折磨'),
  ('extraneous', 'adj.', '多餘的、無直接關係的', 'not belonging to or directly connected with the subject or matter being dealt with', 'She sped up the process by eliminating all extraneous steps. 藉由刪除所有多餘的步驟，他加快了流程', array['impertinent', 'inapposite', 'irrelevant']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'extra 額外的', 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 19'),
  ('extrapolate', 'v.', '推斷', 'sth (fml) (mathematics) calculate (an unknown quantity) approximately from known values or measurements', 'From the wounds of these women, we can extrapolate that they were killed by the same serial killer.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 43'),
  ('extravagant', 'adj.', '誇大的；奢侈的、揮霍的', 'exceeding the limits of reason or necessity; using or spending too much; (of actions) showing this tendency', 'The company has been making extravagant claims about the drug''s effectiveness. 這公司對於藥效有誇大的說詞', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'extra(超出) + vag(走) + ant', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 9'),
  ('exuberant', 'adj.', '熱情的、豐富的、繁茂的 n. exuberance', 'overflowing with happiness and excitement; very lively and cheerful', 'His exuberant personality makes him fun to be around.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 15'),
  ('exude', 'v.', '散發、流露', '(sth) (from/through sth) (of drops of liquid, etc) come or pass out slowly; ooze out', 'former ministers exude optimism', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 51'),
  ('fable', null, '寓言、傳說', null, null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 28 / 字根 fa 說 / 提示 fame 名聲'),
  ('fabricate', null, '偽造；杜撰', 'invent, create; to make up for the purpose of deception', 'a story fabricated to sell magazines 為了銷售雜誌而造假的故事', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 19'),
  ('fabulous', 'adj.', '非常好的', 'incredibly great', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 28 / 字根 fa 說 / 提示 fame 名聲'),
  ('facetious', 'adj.', '輕浮的、好開玩笑的', 'intended to be amusing, often inappropriately', 'Diplo then set off a stream of response tweets, rich with memes and facetious apologies. Diplo接著送出一連串的充滿著梗圖和 玩笑道歉的推特 // a facetious remark 玩笑的言辭', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'face(臉) + ous(多...的) → 臉很多 → 扮開心扮難過逗人笑 → 好開玩笑的', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 13'),
