  ('impromptu', 'adj.', '事先無準備地、即席地', 'adv without preparation, rehearsal or thought in advance', 'She gave an impromptu speech at the wedding, but it was so well-received that people thought she had rehearsed it. 她在婚禮上臨 時發表了一篇演講，但它非常受到好評，以至於人們以為她已經排練過了。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 111 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('improvise', 'v.', '即興創作、即興表演', 'compose or play (music), speak or act without previous preparation', 'If an actor forgets his words, he has to improvise. 演員要是忘記臺詞，就必須即興演出 an improvised speech 即興演講', array['extemporize']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'im(不) + pro(前) + vise(看) → 沒有預先看過', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 11'),
  ('imprudent', 'adj.', '不謹慎的、輕率的、魯莽的', 'not wise or discreet; not prudent', 'It''s politically imprudent to stir up such controversy during an election year. 在選舉年掀起如此爭議是政治上的輕率', '{}'::text[], array['prudent']::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 11'),
