  ('incessant', 'adj.', '不停的、連續的、持續不斷的', 'not stopping; continual', 'Her incessant complaining is tiresome to everyone. 她沒完沒了的抱怨使每個人都厭煩。', array['constant', 'unremitting', 'continual', 'endless']::text[], array['sporadic(偶爾發生的)']::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 36'),
  ('inchoate', 'adj.', '剛開始的、起初的、未完的', 'just begun and therefore not fully formed or developed', 'Company''s plans were still inchoate and needed more discussion before they could be implemented successfully. 公司的計劃還是 不成熟的，需要更多的討論才能成功實施。', array['budding', 'inceptive', 'incipient', 'nascent']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'inch(英寸) + cho(音讀口) → 口僅一英寸 → 起初的', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 52'),
