  ('incite', 'v.', '激勵、激起、煽動', 'sb urge or persuade sb to do sth by making him very angry or excited', 'The news incited widespread fear and paranoia. (妄想症；偏執狂)', array['stir up', 'spur on', 'urge on']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'exciting 刺激的', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 17 / 字根 cit: speak, summon 說、召喚 / 提示 recite 背誦、朗誦'),
  ('incongruous', 'adj.', '不協調的、不一致的；不得體的', 'strange because not in harmony with the surrounding features; out of place', 'incongruous manners 失當不得體的舉止 // incongruous colors 不協調的顏色', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 16'),
  ('inconsequential', 'adj.', '不重要的; 微不足道的', 'trivial or irrelevant; not important', 'He is very adamant about signing the peace treaty. Your opposing opinions will only prove inconsequential. 他很堅決地要簽署和平 協議。你的反對意見將證明為微不足道的', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 11'),
  ('incontrovertible', 'adj.', '無疑的、明白的', 'so obvious and certain that it cannot be disputed or denied', 'The evidence presented was incontrovertible. 提出的證據無可爭議。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 64'),
