  ('inflate', 'v.', '使充氣、使膨脹', 'to expand or increase abnormally or imprudently; sth (with sth) fill (a tyre, balloon, etc) with air or gas', 'The company''s profits were inflated by accounting fraud. 公司的利潤因會計欺詐而被誇大。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 58'),
  ('inflict', 'v.', '給予（打擊）、使遭受（損傷等）', 'sth cause (a blow, penalty, etc) to be suffered (by sb)', 'Red imported fire ants are characterized by an aggressive defensive behavior and can inflict a painful sting when disturbed. 使招致 疼痛的刺蜇', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 33 / 字根 flict 打擊 / 提示 conflict 衝突'),
  ('influx', 'n.', '注入、湧入', 'arrival of people or things, esp suddenly and in large numbers or quantities', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 33 / 字根 flu 流 / 提示 fluid 流體的、易變的'),
  ('infuse', 'v.', '注入；灌輸', 'sth into sb/sth; sb/sth with sth put into sb/sth; fill sb/sth with (a quality)', 'She decided to infuse her cooking oil with herbs for added flavor. 她決定給烹飪油添加香草以增加風味。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 39'),
  ('ingenious', 'adj.', '聰明的、有發明天才的', 'clever at finding new or simple solutions for complex problems', 'The ingenious girl made a radio set for herself. 這個聰明的女孩為自己做了一臺收音機', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 10'),
