  ('insatiable', 'adj.', '不知足的、貪得無厭的', 'that cannot be satisfied; very greedy', 'The United States depends on Latin American gold to feed insatiable demand from its jewelry, bullion and electronics industries. — miamiherald', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 45'),
