  ('insidious', 'adj.', '隱藏詭計的', 'spreading or acting gradually and unnoticed but with harmful effects', 'an insidious enemy; an insidious plot', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'in(內) + sid(坐) + ious // Insidious comes from a Latin word for "ambush" (insidiae), which is fitting, as this word often carries the meanings "deceitful," "stealthy," or "harmful in an imperceptible fashion." - Merriam Webster', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 46'),
  ('insinuate', 'v.', '譏諷；暗示；滲入', 'sth suggest sth (to sb) unpleasantly and indirectly', '"It is one thing to question the official story, and another entirely to make wild accusations or insinuate that I''m a superhero." ― Tony Stark', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 79 / 字根 sinu 彎曲 / 提示 sinuous 蜿蜒的、迂迴的'),
  ('insipid', 'adj.', '沒有味道的、清淡的；乏味的', 'having almost no taste or flavour', 'What we know as "popular" or "mass" culture has always conformed to the most insipid prejudices. - Joyce Carol Oates, The Profane Art, 1983 我們所知的熱門或大眾文化總是順服於最乏味的成見', array['flat', 'flavorless', 'savorless', 'tasteless', 'unsavory']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'in(不) + sip(喝) + id → 不好喝的 → 乏味的', 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 17'),
  ('insolent', 'adj.', '粗魯無禮的、傲慢的', 'extremely rude, esp in expressing contempt', 'He was insolent in his manner. 他態度傲慢無禮', array['rude', 'insulting', 'impudent', 'arrogant', 'haughty', 'defiant', 'bold']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'in (=not) + sol(習慣) → 不習慣禮節 → 顯得粗魯、傲慢', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 14'),
  ('insouciance', 'n.', '無憂無慮、不注意、不在乎', 'state of being unconcerned, esp in a light-hearted way; nonchalance', 'wandered (漫步) into the meeting with complete insouciance (完全地漫不經心) to the fact that she was late', array['nonchalance']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 36'),
