  ('lax', 'adj.', '鬆散的、不嚴格的 花錢', 'not sufficiently strict or severe; negligent 3lay out', 'Facebook''s lax data-privacy rules They had already laid out a substantial sum for the wedding. 為婚禮花費了很多錢 We''ll need to lay out a lot of money to buy all the materials for the project. 花很多錢買材料', array['careless', 'derelict', 'disregardful', 'neglecting', 'negligent', 'remiss', 'slack']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 52'),
