  ('notoriety', 'n.', '惡名昭彰、聲名狼藉', 'fame for being bad in some way', 'the city''s notoriety for corrupt and incompetent government 本城市貪汙腐敗和無能政府的昭彰惡名', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 17'),
  ('nova', 'n.', '新星', 'a transient astronomical event that causes the sudden appearance of a bright, apparently "new" star, that slowly fades over several weeks or many months - Wikipedia', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 56 / 字根 nov 新 / 提示 novelty 新奇、新奇的事物'),
  ('novelty', 'n.', '新奇、新奇的事物', 'quality of being novel; newness; strangeness', 'But novelties (of a self-driving vehicle) wear off (磨去；麻木), and people will always prefer convenience and affordability. — Andrew J. Hawkins, The Verge', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 41'),
  ('novice', 'n.', '新手、初學者', 'person who is new and inexperienced in a job, situation, etc; beginner', 'This plant can be difficult for novice gardeners to grow.', array['apprentice', 'fledgling', 'neophyte', 'tyro']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 61'),
  ('noxious', 'adj.', '有害的、有毒的', 'harmful; poisonous', 'Noxious chemicals are found in the river water. 河水裡發現了有毒化學物品。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 61'),
  ('nuance', 'n.', '細微差異', 'subtle difference in meaning, colour, feeling, etc', 'nuances of language', array['shading']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 10'),
  ('nullify', 'v.', '使無效、廢棄、取消', 'make (an agreement, etc) lose its legal force', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 57 / 字根 nul, nil 無、沒有 / 提示 null 無效的、等於零的'),
  ('numinous', 'adj.', '神祕的；神聖的；超自然的', 'SUPERNATURAL, MYSTERIOUS; filled with a sense of the presence of divinity : HOLY', '"The ancient temple was a numinous place, with its dimly lit halls, burning incense, and the feeling of the divine that seemed to permeate every corner. 古老的寺廟是一個神聖的場所，其昏暗的大廳、燃燒的香煙和彷彿滲透每個角落的神聖氛圍， 使它成為一個神秘而崇敬的場所。', array['mystic', 'occult', 'weird']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 115 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('obdurate', 'adj.', '固執的、頑固的；頑抗的；抵抗的', 'impossible to change; stubborn; resistant to persuasion or softening influences', 'an obdurate opponent 頑抗的對手 // obdurate defense 頑抗的防禦', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 37'),
  ('obeisance', 'n.', '尊重、敬禮', 'deep bow (of respect or obedience)', 'The prince demanded that all visitors pay obeisance to him by bowing low before him. 王子要求所有的訪客都向他深深地鞠躬 表示敬意。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'obey', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 115 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('obfuscate', 'v.', '使困惑、使迷糊', '(deliberately) make (sth) confused or difficult to understand', 'A top-notch lawyer is able to spin, twist, and obfuscate complicated issues in such a manner that the judge thinks he has an unbiased understanding of the issue. 頂尖律師能夠扭曲甚至混淆複雜議題使得法官覺得他對於issue有個不偏倚的了解', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 5'),
  ('objection', 'n.', '厭惡、反對', '(expression of a) feeling of dislike, disapproval or opposition', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'ob(反) + ject(拋、扔) + ion → 反扔過去 → 厭惡', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 41 / 字根 ject 拋、扔 / 提示 eject 趕出、射出'),
  ('objective', 'adj.', '客觀的', 'not influenced by personal feelings or opinions; unbiased; fair', 'A judge must give an objective opinion. 評判員必須發表公正的意見', '{}'::text[], array['subjective 主觀的']::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 10'),
  ('objurgate', null, '申斥、痛罵', null, null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 42 / 字根 jur 發誓、法律 / 提示 jury 陪審團'),
  ('obligatory', 'adj.', '強制性的、義務的', 'required by rule, law or custom; compulsory', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 44 / 字根 lig 綁 / 提示 religion 宗教'),
  ('oblique', 'adj.', '斜的、間接的、不坦率的', 'not straightforward : INDIRECT; not horizontal or vertical; sloping; slanting', 'She made several oblique references to the current financial situation. 拐彎抹角地提及目前的財務狀況', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 53'),
  ('obliterate', 'v.', '塗掉、擦掉', 'remove all signs of (sth); rub or blot out', 'The heavy rain obliterated all footprints.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'ob(反) + liter(文字) + ate → 擦掉文字', 2, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 45 / 字根 liter 字母、文字 / 提示 illiterate 文盲的'),
  ('oblivious', 'adj.', '未察覺的；健忘的', 'of/to sth unaware of or not noticing sth; having no memory of sth', 'The manager kept reading, entirely oblivious of his wife''s presence. 經理繼續念他的書，完全沒注意到他太太在那兒 // Mother has become quite oblivious after the illness. 這次病後，媽媽變得特別健忘', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 20'),
  ('obnoxious', 'adj.', '令人不愉快的、可憎的', 'very unpleasant; nasty; offensive', 'He said some really obnoxious things about his ex-girlfriend at the party.', array['offensive', 'nasty', 'repulsive', 'disgusting', 'loathsome', 'vile', 'despicable', 'contemptible']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 34'),
  ('obsequious', 'adj.', '逢迎的、諂媚的', '(to sb) too willing to obey or serve; too respectful (esp in the hope of getting a reward or favour from sb)', 'obsequious shop assistants 逢迎奉承的店員', array['fawning']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 23'),
  ('observant', 'adj.', '注意的、當心的；嚴格遵守(宗教教條)的', 'paying strict attention : WATCHFUL; careful in observing rites, laws, or customs : MINDFUL', 'pious and religiously observant (嚴格遵守的) families — Sidney Hook', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 63'),
  ('obsolescent', 'adj.', '逐漸被廢棄的、即將過時的', 'becoming out of date; going out of use', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 79 / 字根 sol 習慣於 / 提示 obsolete 廢棄的、淘汰的、過時的'),
  ('obsolete', 'adj.', '廢棄的、淘汰的、過時的', 'no longer used; out of date', 'an obsolete technology 一個過時的科技 // an obsolete word 一個廢棄不再用的字', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 23'),
  ('obstinate', 'adj.', '固執的、倔強的；難以改變的', 'refusing to change one''s opinion or chosen course of action; stubborn', 'the obstinate problem of unemployment', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 23'),
  ('obtrude', 'v.', '突出、強加', '(on/upon sb/sth) (fml ) force (oneself, one''s opinions, ideas, etc) upon sb/sth, esp when unwanted', 'The noisy neighbor continued to obtrude into my life with their loud music and constant parties. 吵鬧的鄰居繼續透過他們的大聲 音樂和持續的派對來干擾我的生活。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 48'),
  ('obtrusive', 'adj.', '唐突的、冒昧的', 'very noticeable or obvious; inclined to obtrude', 'Retweeting yourself frequently is a casual way to slip your content back into people''s timelines without being too obtrusive. Brands have known this for a long time. — Casey Newton, The Verge', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 89 / 字根 trud, trus 伸、伸出 / 提示 intrude 強加於、闖入'),
  ('obviate', 'v.', '排除、消除（困難）', 'remove (sth); get rid of', 'A parachute can be used to obviate disaster. // The new medical treatment obviates the need for surgery. 排除了手術的需求', array['avoid', 'prevent']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'ob: against + via 路', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 9'),
  ('occidental', 'adj.', '西方的', 'western', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '太陽落下的地方', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 12 / 字根 cad, cid, cas 落下 / 提示 accidental 偶然發生的'),
  ('occlude', null, '使閉塞', 'to close up or block off:OBSTRUCT', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 18 / 字根 clud, clus, claus 關閉 / 提示 close 關閉'),
  ('occult', 'adj.', '難以理解的、奧祕的', 'only for those with special knowledge or powers; hidden, secret', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 21 / 字根 cult 宗派 / 提示 cult 迷信、狂熱者'),
  ('odious', 'adj.', '可憎的、可惡的', 'disgusting; hateful', null, array['detestable']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'odi︰奧迪，ous 多 → 他有很多奧迪 → 可惡的', 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 115 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('odoriferous', null, '有味道的、臭的', 'giving off an order', 'The odoriferous smell emanating from the garbage can was unbearable. 散發惡臭的垃圾桶讓人難以忍受。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'odor(氣味) + i + fer(帶來) + ous → 有氣味的', 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 58'),
  ('officious', 'adj.', '好管閒事的、愛發命令的、愛給忠告的', 'too ready or willing to give orders, offer advice or help, or use one''s authority; bossy and interfering', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], '形近officer(官員) → 官字兩個口 → 愛管閒事的', 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 115 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
  ('omen', 'n.', '預兆', '(event regarded as a) sign that sth good or bad will happen in the future', 'a good omen || The dark clouds were considered a bad omen.', array['presage']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 57 / 字根 omin 預兆、不祥 / 提示 ominous 預兆的、不祥的'),
  ('ominous', 'adj.', '兇兆的、不祥的', 'OMINOUS implies having a menacing, alarming character foreshadowing evil or disaster // suggesting that sth bad is about to happen; threatening', 'The demise of the main character five minutes into the film sets an ominous tone. — Jennifer Jhon (on Avengers: Infinity War)', array['inauspicious', 'menacing', 'portentous', 'sinister', 'threatening']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 42'),
  ('omnipotent', 'adj.', '全能的、萬能的', 'having unlimited or very great power', 'an omnipotent deity (神)', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 62'),
  ('omniscient', 'adj.', '無所不知的、博識的', 'knowing everything', 'the narrator seems an omniscient person who tells us about the characters and their relations — Ira Konigsberg', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'omni(全) + sci(知道) + ent // omnipotent全能 (pot力量); omnipresent 無所不在', 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 63'),
  ('onerous', 'adj.', '繁重的、麻煩的', 'needing effort; burdensome', 'She found the duties of motherhood onerous. 作為母親責任繁重', array['burdensome', 'tough']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 2, 2, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 61'),
  ('opalescent', 'adj.', '發乳白光的', 'changing colour like an opal; iridescent', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 2, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 57 / 字根 opa 不透明 / 提示 opaque 不透明的、難懂的'),
  ('opaque', 'adj.', '不透明的、難懂的', 'not allowing light to pass through; not transparent', 'bottles filled with a pale opaque liquid 蒼白不透明液體', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 3'),
  ('opportune', 'adj.', '恰好的、適宜的', '(of time) suitable or favourable for a purpose', 'His startup arrives at an opportune time, as shoppers are keen on value. — Chavie Lieber, Vox', array['seasonable', 'timely', 'well-timed']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 43'),
  ('opportunistic', null, '機會主義的、投機取巧的', null, 'So why is our government, while ignoring truly needy factions, playing butler (男管家) to an already rich, opportunistic, overindulged (過度溺愛的) (airline) industry? — Mitch Albom (Guess who the government wants to help? The airlines")', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 43'),
  ('opprobrium', 'n.', '譴責；辱罵 opprobrious 譴責的', 'public disgrace and shame', 'The bombing of the church was met with widespread opprobrium. 轟炸教堂受到廣大的責難', array['infamy', 'reproach', 'shame']::text[], '{}'::text[], 'oppo 手機品質受到責難 (純屬虛構)', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 15'),
  ('optical', null, '眼睛的、視力的', null, null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 58 / 字根 opt 選擇、視力、希望 / 提示 adopt 採取、採納'),
  ('optimal', null, '最佳的、最理想的', null, 'There is no strict consensus in the medical community regarding how much protein is optimal for good health, though research is ongoing.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 42'),
  ('optimistic', 'adj.', '樂觀的', 'expecting the best; confident', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 58 / 字根 opt 選擇、視力、希望 / 提示 adopt 採取、採納'),
  ('opulent', 'adj.', '豐饒的、華麗的、奢侈的', 'having or showing signs of great wealth', 'The Chairman Suites, at $25,000 per night, were the most opulent the Palazzo had to offer. 主席套房是最奢華的房款', array['affluent', 'loaded', 'wealthy', 'well-off', 'well-to-do']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 42'),
