  ('shackle', 'n.', 'n. 腳鐐 v. 束縛', 'either of a pair of metal rings linked by a chain, used for fastening a prisoner''s wrists or ankles together', 'Ortiz, who was shirtless and still had a shackle on one of his legs, dashed into the 14th Street subway station at Seventh Avenue.', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 120 / 字根 vulg 普通 / 提示 vulgar 粗俗的、下流的'),
