  ('thrift', null, '節省、節儉', 'careful management especially of money', 'Through hard work and thrift they sent all of their children to college. 透過努力與勤儉，他們將所有小孩送去大學唸書', array['economy', 'frugality']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 4, 4, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 24'),
  ('thwart', 'v.', '阻撓、阻礙', 'prevent doing what he intends; oppose (a plan, etc) successfully', 'A greater police presence in that neighborhood might thwart some criminals and inadvertently save lives. 更大的見警率應能阻撓 罪犯且不經意地拯救生命', '{}'::text[], array['foment(煽動)', 'bolster(支持)']::text[], '字源於"twist" 扭曲 → 阻撓', 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 3'),
  ('timorous', 'adj.', '膽小的、膽怯的', 'timid', null, array['timid']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 87 / 字根 tim 害怕、恐懼 / 提示 timid 膽小的、易受驚的'),
  ('tonic', 'n.', '使人精神振奮的、滋補的', 'medicine that gives strength or energy, taken after illness or when tired', 'After a long day at work, she found a tonic in a warm bath. 工作了一整天後，她在溫熱的浴缸中找到了恢復元氣的方法。', '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], 'Tonic water is often used as a drink mixer for cocktails, especially gin and tonic. Vodka tonic is also popular. Tonic water with lemon or lime flavor added is known as bitter lemon or bitter lime, respectively. - Wikipedia', 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 86 / 字根 tend, tens, tent 拉、伸 / 提示 extend 延伸'),
