  ('transient', 'adj.', '短暫的、轉瞬即逝的、一時的', 'lasting for only a short time; brief; fleeting', 'Chemotherapy (化療) almost always causes transient nausea 片刻的噁心 and hair loss 掉髮. // transient beauty 短暫的美麗', array['transitory', 'ephemeral']::text[], array['lasting', 'persistent(持久的)']::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 11'),
  ('transitional', 'adj.', '轉變的、變遷的', 'a transitional stage', null, '{}'::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 1, 1, 'Mason 2000 / Mason 2000 PDF page 41 / 字根 it 走 / 提示 transit 通過、運輸'),
  ('transitory', 'adj.', '短暫的、瞬息的', 'lasting for only a short time; transient', 'No matter how slight or transitory, the symptoms of a mild stroke are warnings that must not be ignored. 無論多小多短暫，中風的 病癥是絕對不能被忽視的警告', array['temporary']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 10'),
