  ('trenchant', 'adj.', '（言辭）犀利的、鋒利的', 'strongly and effectively expressed; penetrating', '(1) trenchant commentary (2) Because rap and hip-hop offer such trenchant commentary on contemporary issues, they are often said to be sharp-edged musical genres.', array['incisive', 'penetrating']::text[], '{}'::text[], '音讀「穿透的」 → 言詞犀利的、鋒利的', 3, 3, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 48'),
  ('trepidation', 'n.', '恐懼、惶恐', 'great worry or fear about sth unpleasant that may happen', 'The return of inflation to the Fed''s 2% target in March and April has removed some of the trepidation about raising rates. - WSJ ，在 三月和四月回歸到Fed (美國聯準會) 2% 通膨目標後，移除了大家對於升息的害怕恐懼。', array['anxiety', 'dread', 'fear', 'fearfulness', 'fright', 'horror', 'panic', 'scare', 'terror']::text[], '{}'::text[], null, 5, 5, 'Mason 1000; Mason 2000 / primary: Mason 1000 PDF page 5'),
